column12: MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEM FOR EVALUATION OF CHEMOTHERAPEUTIC AND IMMUNOTHERAPEUTIC DRUGS
column13: Systems and methods for conducting assays on tissue fragment samples including providing a suspension maintaining pump, and a plurality of fluid reservoirs, wherein the fluid reservoirs are configured to hold a volume of fluid. The fluid reservoirs are fluidically coupled to a microfluidic assay chip, wherein the microfluidic assay chip includes a plurality of parallel assay channels, a first inlet port for introduction of a tissue fragment sample into the microfluidic assay ship, and a second inlet port coupled to the fluid reservoir. Each channel of the microfluidic assay chip also includes a retention barrier configured to trap the tissue fragment sample such that the fluid perfuses through the tissue sample, as well as an outlet port fluidically coupled to a waste receptacle.

column12: Synchronizing transaction ambient state among multiple transaction managers
column13: The present invention extends to methods, systems, and computer program products for synchronizing ambient state among multiple transaction managers. A coordinating transaction manager establishes transaction ambient state for an application initiated transaction. The coordinating transaction manager sends and a subordinate transaction manager receives a pointer to an ambient state delegate. The subordinate transaction manager sends a request to invoke the ambient state delegate to the coordinating transaction manager in response to receiving an operation. The coordinating transaction manager invokes the ambient state delegate to format the transaction ambient state for the subordinate transaction manager. The coordinating transaction manager sends and the subordinate transaction manager receives the formatted transaction ambient state such that the subordinate transaction manager can appropriately process the operation within the scope of the transaction. The subordinate transaction manager utilizes the formatted transaction ambient state to appropriately process the operation within the scope of the transaction.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR MAPPING A DOMAIN MODELING LANGUAGE TO A RELATIONAL STORE
column13: A method and system for mapping between constructs in a domain modeling language and a relational storage language is provided. A source code authored in a source language is received and a set of constructs in the source code are identified. The set of constructs in the source code are mapped to a set of constructs in a target language. The source code is then compiled into a target code authored in the target language such that one of the source code or target code include a declarative constraint-based and/or order-independent execution model.

column12: RIB SUPPORT FOR WING PANELS
column13: An innovative wing structure provides ribs to support skin panels without an attachment between the rib and the stringer free flange or the web. The support is provided by rib shear ties installed directly to the stringer skin flange. The rib incorporates a cut away to allow the stringer to pass through the rib. The composite stringer is an ‘I’ section and is stable under compression, not requiring mechanical methods to prevent rolling over.

column12: Rib support for wing panels

In one advantageous embodiment, the aircraft structure (400,526) may have a rib (506-510), a plurality of stringers (512-522), and a set of shear ties (600,602). The plurality of stringers may have skin flanges (608-612) at ends of the plurality of stringers capable of being fastened to skin (524) for the aircraft structure. The set of shear ties may extend from the rib and have a set of elongate members (624-635) in which the set of elongate members are attached to the plurality of stringers.

column12: AIRCRAFT STRUCTURE AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a structural element provided with an improved load passage when supporting a rib of a wing panel.

SOLUTION: This aircraft structure may have the rib 400, a plurality of longitudinal penetrating materials 412 and a pair of shear ties 406. The plurality of longitudinal penetrating materials 412 may have outer plate flanges fastened to an outer plate 416 for the aircraft structure at end parts of the plurality of longitudinal penetrating materials 412. The pair of shear ties 406 are capable of being extended from the rib 400 and having a pair of elongate members. In the pair of shear ties 406, the pair of elongate members are mounted on the plurality of longitudinal penetrating materials 412.

column12: Method for treating infectious organisms normally considered to be resistant to an antimicrobial drug
column13: The present invention relates to compositions of submicron- to micron-size particles of antimicrobial agents. More particularly the invention relates to a composition of an antimicrobial agent that renders the agent potent against organisms normally considered to be resistant to the agent. The composition comprises an aqueous suspension of submicron- to micron-size particles containing the agent coated with at least one surfactant selected from the group consisting of: ionic surfactants, non-ionic surfactants, biologically derived surfactants, and amino acids and their derivatives. The particles have a volume-weighted mean particle size of less than 5 μm as measured by laser diffractometry.

column12: formulação para tornar uma droga antimicrobiana potente contra organismos normalmente considerados serem resistentes à droga
column13: "FORMULAçãO PARA TORNAR UMA DROGA ANTI-MICROBIANA POTENTE CONTRA ORGANISMOS NORMALMENTE CONSIDERADOS SEREM RESISTENTES à DROGA". A presente invenção refere-se a composições de partículas de tamanho submícron a mícron de agentes antimicrobianos. Mais particularmente a invenção refere-se a uma composição de um agente antimicrobiano que torna o agente potente contra organismos normalmente considerados serem resistentes ao agente. A composição compreende uma suspensão aquosa de partículas de tamanho submícron a mícron contendo o agente revestidas com pelo menos um tensoativo selecionado do grupo consistindo em: tensoativos iónicos, tensoativos não-iónicos, tensoativos derivados biologicamente, e aminoácidos e seus derivados. As partículas têm um tamanho de partícula médio de volume pesado de menos que 5 <109>m como medido por difratometria de laser.

column13: Foreliggende oppfinnelse gjelder preparater av partikler av submikrometer- til mikrometerstørrelse av antimikrobielle midler. Nærmere bestemt gjelder oppfinnelsen et preparat av et antimikrobielt middel som gjør midlet aktivt mot organismer som normalt anses å være resistente overfor midlet. Preparatet omfatter en vandig suspensjon av partikler av submikrometer- til mikrometerstørrelse som inneholder midlet, belagt med minst én surfaktant utvalgt fra gruppen som består av ioniske surfaktanter, ikke-ioniske surfaktanter, biologisk avledede surfaktanter og aminosyrer og deres derivater. Partiklene har en volumveiet gjennomsnittelig partikkelstørrelse på mindre enn 5 (m, målt ved laserdiffraktometri.

column12: VAPORIZER DEVICE COMPRISING ONE OR MORE HEATER ELEMENTS
column13: To provide a vaporizer device comprising a heating element and a heating system capable of efficiently and effectively heating one or more types of volatile materials.SOLUTION: A vaporizer device for generating a mixed aerosol which can be sucked comprises: a body comprising a penetrating ventilation flue; a first cartridge container configured to have a first volatile material; a second cartridge container configured to have a second volatile material; a first heater for heating the first volatile material and forming a first aerosol which can be sucked; a second heater for heating the second volatile material and forming a second aerosol which can be sucked. The ventilation flue comprises: one or more heaters which extend adjacently the first heater and the second heater, and heat one or more volatile materials for forming a mixed aerosol to be sucked by a user from an end part by mixing the first aerosol and second aerosol which can be sucked.SELECTED DRAWING: None

column12: CARTRIDGE-BASED HEAT NOT BURN VAPORIZER
column13: A vaporizer device including a vaporizer cartridge configured to efficiently and effectively heat a non-liquid vaporizable material is described. The vaporizer cartridge may include a heating element configured to vaporize the vaporizable material by delivery of heat to the vaporizable material. The cartridge may include a cartridge contact in electrical communication with the heating element. The cartridge contact may be configured to couple to a receptacle contact along a vaporizer body of the vaporizer device having a power source to allow power to pass from the power source to the heating element. The heating element can include electrically resistive features such that current traveling along the heating element can cause the heating element to increase in temperature to within a desired temperature range. Related systems, methods, and articles of manufacture are also described.

column12: RECLOSABLE CONTAINER LID
column13: A reclosable lid 10 for a container holding a flowable substance has a first piece or cover 12, and a movable second piece or disk 50. The cover 10 has a top wall 14, a side wall 16 and a mounting portion 22 for connecting the lid 10 on the container. The cover 12 has an opening 28 adapted to permit the flow of the substance through the lid 10 . The cover 12 further includes a slot 30 located in the top wall 14. The disk 50 has at least one aperture 78, a post 54, and a projection 52. The aperture 78 and the projection 52 are ea ch cooperatively dimensioned with the opening 28. The post 54 is adapted to be received by th e slot 30 in the cover 12. The disk 50 is movable between a first position wherein at least a portion of the projection 52 is received in the opening 28 in the first position, and a second position wherein the aperture 78 is aligned with the opening 28 in the second positio n. A support ledge 102 and a support edge 104 on an inner surface 100 of the cover 12 are adapted to provide rotatable support to the disk 50.

column12: TAPA DE RECIPIENTE QUE PUEDE VOLVER A CERRARSE
column13: Una tapa que puede volver a cerrarse 10 para un recipiente que contiene una sustancia liquida, tiene una primera pieza o tapa 12, y una segunda pieza movible o disco 50. La tapa 10 tiene una pared superior 14, una pared lateral 16 y una porcion como montadura 22 para conectar la tapa 10 sobre el recipiente. La tapa 12 ademas incluye una ranura 30 localizada en la pared superior 14. El disco 50 tiene al menos una abertura 78, un poste 54 y una saliente 52. La abertura 78 y la saliente 52 tienen dimensiones cooperativas con la abertura 28. El poste 54 se adapta para ser recibido por la ranura 30 de la tapa 12. El disco 50 es movible entre una primera posicion en donde al menos una porcion de la saliente 52 es recibida en la apertura 28 en la primera posicion, y una segunda posicion en donde la abertura 78 esta alineada con la abertura 28 en la segunda posicion.

column12: Lokk for beholder som kan benyttes flere ganger.
column13: Et gjenlukkbart lokk 10 for en beholder som inneholder en strømbar substans omfatter en første del eller et deksel 12 og en bevegelig andre del eller en plate 50. Dekselet 10 har en toppvegg 14, en sidevegg 16 og en festedel 22 for å feste lokket 10 på beholderen. Dekselet 12 har en åpning 28 innrettet for å muliggjøre strømning av substansen gjennom lokket 10. Dekselet 12 omfatter videre en slisse 30 tilveiebrakt i toppveggen 14. Platen 50 har minst ett hull 78, en oppstikker 54 og en uthevning 52. Hullet 78 og uthevningen 52 er dimensjonert i overensstemmelse med åpningen 28. Oppstikkeren. 54 er innrettet for å bli mottatt i slissen 30 i dekselet 12. Platen 50 er bevegelig mellom en første posisjon der i hvert fall en andel av uthevningen 52 er mottatt i åpningen 28 og en andre posisjon der hullet 78 er linjeført med åpningen 28. En støtteskulder 102 og en støttekant 104 på en innvendig overflate 100 av dekselet 12 er innrettet for å gi roterbar understøtte for platen 50.

The cover 12  has an opening 28  adapted to permit the flow of the substance through the lid 10 . The cover 12  further includes a slot 30  located in the top wall 14 . column12: Reclosable container lid
column13: A reclosable lid 10 for a container holding a flowable substance is disclosed. The lid has a cover 12 for attachment to the container, with the cover having an opening and a support member extending inward from an inner surface of a side wall. The cover 12 also has an opening 28 to permit the flow of the substance through the lid and a further slot 30. A movable disk 50 is rotatably supported by the support member. The disk 50 has at least one aperture, and an actuator 54. The actuator 54 protrudes through the slot 30 to allow manipulation of the actuator to cause rotation of the disk between a first closed position and a second open position where the opening 28 is aligned with the aperture in the disk to allow the substance to flow through the lid.

column12: Tampa para recipiente capaz de ser fechada novamente
column13: "TAMPA PARA RECIPIENTE CAPAZ DE SER FECHADA NOVAMENTE". A presente invenção refere-se à tampa capaz de ser fechada novamente (10) para um recipiente que retém uma substância fluida apresenta uma primeira peça ou cobertura (12), e uma segunda peça ou disco (50). A cobertura (10) apresenta uma parede de topo (14), uma parede lateral (16) e uma porção de montagem (22) para conectar a tampa (10) no recipiente. A cobertura (12) apresenta uma abertura (28) adaptada para permitir o fluxo da substância através da tampa (10). A cobertura (12) adicionalmente inclui uma fenda (30) localizada na parede de topo (14). O disco (50) apresenta pelo menos um orifício (78), um montante vertical (54), e uma projeção (52). O orifício (78) e a projeção (52) são cada qual cooperativamente dimensionados com a abertura (28). O montante vertical (54) é adaptado para ser recebido pela fenda (30) na cobertura (12). O disco (50) é móvel entre uma primeira posição, na qual pelo menos uma porção da projeção (52) é recebida na abertura (28) na primeira posição, e uma segunda posição, na qual o orifício (78) é alinhado com a abertura (28) na segunda posição. Uma saliência de suporte (102) e uma borda de suporte (104) na superfície interna (100) da cobertura (12) são adaptadas para proverem suporte giratório ao disco (50).

column12: RECLOSABLE CONTAINER LID
column13: A reclosable lid (310) for a container holding a flowable substance has a cover (312) and a rotatable element (50) rotatably supported by the cover (312). The cover (3l2) has an opening (28) and a slot (30) located in a top wall (14) of the cover (312). The cover (312) also has a tab (323) extending outward from a portion of the cover (312). The rotatable element (50) has at least one aperture (78) and an actuator (54) that is accessible through the slot (30). The element (50) is moveable by manipulation of the actuator (54) between a first position wherein the aperture (78) is misaligned with the opening (28), and a second position wherein the aperture (78) is aligned wit h the opening (28). The cover (312) has at least one support member (l02) extending radially inward from an inner surface (100) of the cover (312), wherein the support member (102) rotatably supports the element (50).</SDOAB >

column12: Gjenlukkbart beholderlokk
column13: Et gjenlukkbart lokk (310) for en beholder som kan inneholde en strømmingsdyktig substans har et deksel (312) og et roterbart element (50) som roterbart understøttes av dekslet (312). Dekslet (312) har en åpning (28) og en sliss (30) lokalisert i en toppvegg (14) av dekslet (312). Dekslet (312) har også en flik (323) som strekker seg utover fra en del av dekslet (312). Det roterbare element (50) har minst én apertur (78) og en aktuator (54) som er tilgjengelig gjennom slissen (30). Elementet (50) er bevegelig ved manipulasjon av aktuatoren (54) mellom en første posisjon hvori aper- turen (78) er mistilpasset med åpningen (28), og en andre posisjon, hvori aperturen (78) er innrettet på linje med åpningen (28). Dekslet (312) har minst et støtteelement (102) som strekker seg radielt innover fra en indre overflate (100) av dekslet (312) hvori støtteelementet (102) roterbart understøtter elementet (50).

column12: INTERFACE INFRASTRUCTURE FOR CREATING WEB SERVICE AND PERFORMING CONVERSATION
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an interface infrastructure creating a Web Service and performing conversation.

SOLUTION: A web service name space relates to the infrastructure for realizing creation of various applications. The infrastructure provides a basis for constructing message base applications varied in scale and complication. The infrastructure or a framework provides an API for basic messaging, secure messaging, reliable messaging, and transaction type messaging. In some implementation forms, an associated API is factorized to layers in a name space by a method balancing utility, usability, extensibility, and a version property.
